FBIS3-15003 "drsov041_p_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Karabakh Warns on Azeri Cease-Fire Violation NC0103135994 Yerevan SNARK in English 1045 GMT 1 Mar 94 NC0103135994 Yerevan SNARK Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Stepanakert, March 1 (SNARK)--The Azerbaijani side violated the armistice on cease-fire from 00:00, 1st of March. The armistice was achieved through the mediation of the Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev. The Press-Service of the Karabakh Defense Army told SNARK last night and this morning the positions of the Karabakh troops at some parts of the front, in particular, at the northern Martuninskiy region, were under the artillery shellings. The Karabakh side suffers 3 soldiers wounded. Following the terms of the armistice treaty Karabakh defenders made no retaliative actions. In connection with the action Seyran Oganyan, the Head of the Staff of the Karabakh Defense Army, made a declaration which says that the Karabakh side will have to undertake the adequate measures if Azeris go on with the armistice violations.
